==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hydropneumatic gun carriage
<hw>Hy`dro*pneu*mat"ic gun carriage</hw>. <fld>(Ordnance)</fld> <def>A
disappearing gun carriage in which the recoil is checked by cylinders
containing liquid and air, the air when compressed furnishing the power
for restoring the gun to the firing position. It is used with some
English and European heavy guns.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydropsy</ent>⟦br⟧
